An appellate court ordered the trial of the four officers accused of killing Amadou Diallo to be moved to Albany County, ruling on Thursday that a fair trial would be impossible in the Bronx because of ``the public clamor'' about the case.
The New York Times said in an editorial for Saturday, Dec. 18: The decision by a state appellate court to move the criminal trial of four New York City police officers charged with the killing of Amadou Diallo to Albany County seems unjustified.
A grand jury indicted the plain clothes officers in March after they fired 41 bullets
